<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%>
	   <a name=1002827192473></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f1002827192473><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=1662&mid=1002827192473>Hamed and the Healers</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=1662&mid=1002827192473#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=26549><span id=Scholar>mcoolidge</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>236 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Oct 11th 3:06 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I got this ring last night - I think it's a pretty darn good resist piece. Not great, but certainly good and easily attainable. Once you know where to look. <br><br>Hamed and his PH, "a kerran ahmad shaman", spawn in the underground room. To reach it, go down the stairs in the hut with Melixis, the alchemist. The funny thing about these stairs is that, due to the shape of the room, you can literally be standing in the hut and not realize there's a stairway in there. I know. Trust me.<br><br>The battle itself was kinda funny at level 40. I snare Hamed and start swinging. He tries over and over and over to Root / Waking Sleep me. Resisted 100% of his spells. Get him to half-life very quickly, then the 3 other Shamans in the area begin chain-healing him, with Light Healing. So, its pretty much a standoff. This went on for a LONG time. But, eventually they went OOM and Hamed went down shortly after.<br><br>Got the Ring of Tears, and some random junk. I was pleased I didn't get the other drop, since Hamed or his PH is about a 20 minute spawn. He showed up after 2 PHs.<br><br>Arynduil Greyleaf<br>Ranger of Tunare<br>Erollsi Marr<br>&nbsp;<br>Arynduil<br>A Pathfinder on EMarr<br><br>"In a crowded Universe, when the talking turns to noise, you almost start laughing"</td></tr>
